data.value:
The Kapuche Lake trek, the virgin glacial lake trek route is New trekking route in Nepal which is less crowded in the Annapurna trekking region. The Kapuche glacial lake is located 2546 m. from sea level. An expert says that is shocking to found a glacial lake below 4000m. All glacial lake start from 4000 m. the ice melts from the Annapurna II it is the lowest glacial lake in Nepal.
The Annapurna region is the most popular trekking destination but the Kapuche Lake is an unexplored and less crowded trekking route that starts from Pokhara through the largest Gurung village Sikles which is the most beautiful village that offers an opportunity to see unique their traditional cultural and extraordinary views of the snow-capped mountains.
Kapucke Lake has been declared the lowest altitude glacial lake in the world. The lake 1200 square meters, Kapuche the noun from the Gurung language it refers to the plain surface made of crushed snow and ices. Himalaya Ecological Trekking invites you to join this amazing journey and experience the authentic lifestyle of Nepalese living in the rural midwestern part of Nepal.
